# Security Rules

Follow `.ai/rules/security-rules.md` and `docs/08-security/`.

## Authentication

- JWT access token (15 min, RS256) + refresh token (7 days, httpOnly cookie, rotated)
- Permissions resolved server-side — NOT embedded in JWT claims
- Reference: ADR-005, `docs/04-api/authentication.md`

## Authorization — Matter Walls

```text
IF resource is case-scoped AND user lacks access:
  RETURN 404 Not Found   ← NOT 403
```

- Check RBAC permission first, then matter wall (participant membership)
- ManagingPartner and ComplianceOfficer bypass matter walls for read only
- Reference: ADR-007, `docs/08-security/matter-walls.md`

## Audit

- Every mutating API call → append-only audit log
- Document view/download logged
- AI invocations logged (PII-redacted prompt copy)
- Audit table: INSERT only for application role

## Secrets

- AWS Secrets Manager only — never in code, n8n repo, or logs
- `.env.example` documents keys without values

## AI Security

- PII redaction before LLM calls
- Case-scoped RAG only (filter by case_id)
- No auto-send of AI output to clients or courts

Reference: `.ai/tasks/review-security.md`
